  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Memorial Presenting the Appointment of the Commander of the Northwestern Frontier
  author: Park Ho
  language: eng
  text: |-
    On this day of this month, I received the official dispatch and learned with reverence that the celestial court has bestowed its favor, granting authority over a region. I bow in congratulation.

    Consider then the Great Teacher and Prime Minister: his virtue flows highest and steadfast in counsel, his grace perfected in the middle way. He embodies the noble character of an imperial advisor while wielding the extraordinary talent of a kingly minister. His resolute words and loyal voice guide all affairs toward harmony and clarity; his grand strategies and far-reaching plans ensure peace across the four quarters. Now, sharing the burden of the ten-thousand-chariot throne, he commands the discipline of the Six Armies from below. All the people turn to gaze upon his appointment, celebrating that the granting of the commander's seal has found its worthy bearer. The distant peoples hear and prepare to petition humbly at the gates.

    I, having long inherited such lofty teaching, now undertake the responsibilities of the frontier. My earnest devotion accumulates and grows ever deeper, standing far apart from that of ordinary men.
  footnotes:
    - This is a formal official document presenting the appointment of a regional military commander, written in the elevated style of Classical Chinese court memorials.
    - References to 'Great Teacher and Prime Minister' and the 'Six Armies' follow traditional Chinese administrative and military terminology used in the Korean court.
    - The 'ten-thousand-chariot throne' is a classical expression for imperial sovereignty and the burden of rulership.
